content.description:
A beautiful, steep low cave on the back, Pacific-facing side of the First Block. Start low and left matched at the lowest point on the lip slopey lip and traverse right, jumping to a nice rounded knob and mantle over the lip. Climb the slab up to the top.

Maybe pad the close block behind you.

Something much harder could start under the lip in the cave, probably in the V10 or harder range.
content.protection: A pad for the smaller block below
content.location: Walk to the right past "Front Line" and continue around the smaller block. Walk back into the little cove behind the smaller block to the low cave.

content.description:
Start low an nice, opposing holds and toss to the higher ledge. Work up and a bit left past more ledges. Continue to the top and navigate some loose holds to a nice in-cut to top out.

This was as of early Feb 2020. Tides/seasonality may change this considerably.
content.location: This climbs the northern, vertical face following nice features.
